HEADWORD: Olden
<hw>Old"en</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To grow old; to age.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She had <qex>oldened</qex> in that time.</q>
<rj><qau>Thackeray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

